    - The reference to 'broth' alludes to Liu Bang of the Han dynasty, who when his father was held hostage by Xiang Yu and threatened with being boiled alive, responded with equanimity, saying if his father were cooked to send him some broth—demonstrating supreme indifference to personal loss.
    - Wen Jiao's severing of his robe refers to his leaving his mother's embrace to serve an important diplomatic mission, cutting his sleeve as a symbolic break while maintaining filial duty.
